Arsenal legend, Thierry Henry, has insisted that Liverpool is stronger than Real Madrid ahead of both sides’ Champions League final later this month. Henry also claimed that all European clubs fear Real Madrid and the Los Blancos fear Barcelona. The former France international said this while speaking on CBS Sports in comments carried by Marca. “All European clubs fear Real Madrid and Real Madrid fear Barcelona,” Henry said. “But I think Liverpool will win the Champions League. They’re stronger than Madrid.” Henry netted 51 goals in 123 caps for the France national team and enjoyed a stellar club career that saw him represent Monaco, Juventus, New York Red Bulls, Arsenal and Barcelona. The 44-year-old scored 360 goals in his club career.